an evening with alvaro uribe 58th president of the republic of colombia events at stanford an evening with alvaro uribe 58th president of the republic of colombia facebook twitter email print add to calendar laying the path to peace and democracy alvaro uribe president of colombia from 2002 2010 is known as the man who put the farc on the defensive professionalized colombia's military ended the country's notoriety as the world's kidnap capital and resuscitated the economy join us as he discusses leading a nation through a time of conflict and shares his thoughts on the leadership challenges facing colombia and the rest of latin america sponsored by view from the top global speaker series latin american student association when tuesday february 14 2012 5 15 pm approximate duration of 1 hour s where stanford graduate school of business knight management center cemex auditorium zambrano hall map audience faculty staff students alumni friends members tags lecture reading international public service sponsor graduate school of business contact leadership gsb stanford edu admission free and open to the stanford community please register here permalink http events stanford edu events 308 30853 last modified february 10 2012
